title: Honey Boo Boo Releases Rap Song and Music Video
text:
Comments Alana Thompson shows off her 'Honey Boo Boo Bop' dance moves with Mama June, Sugar Bear, and Pumpkin. 
" Here Comes Honey Boo Boo " family is trying to make a comeback after their reality show was canceled by TLC last year. Alana Thompson, the star of the show, releases a rap song called "Movin' Up" and a music video to accompany the track. The 10-year-old star teams up with her sister Lauryn "Pumpkin" Shannon and viral video artist Adam Barta. In the music video, they along with Mama June and Sugar Bear are seen showing off their "Honey Boo Boo Bop" dance moves. "Started out as a pageant queen/ then on TV doing my thing/ now movin' up in the world/ new fun times with my girls," she raps. "I'm the princess of this castle/ Mama June queen of the house/ Went from something to nothing/ I holler and scream and shout."
